A Calochortus nuttallii is a flowering plant, belonging to the lily family.
The plant is commonly known as Sego lily or Mariposa lily.
It is native to the Western United States and Canada.
The flowers are typically showy, with three white, pink or lavender petals, and prominent yellow stamens.
The leaves are long and narrow, resembling blades of grass.
Calochortus nuttallii is often found in arid or semi-arid habitats, such as dry meadows, sagebrush, or Pinyon-Juniper woodland.
The plant has cultural significance for Native American tribes in the region, who have used it for food and medicinal purposes.
